Package com.cafean.client.values

Class AbstractNumericsModel

  • java.lang.Object
    • com.cafean.client.analysis.GenericObject
      • com.cafean.client.analysis.AbstractModel
        • com.cafean.client.values.AbstractNumericsModel
  • All Implemented Interfaces:
    Checkable, IdentHolder, ModelElement, NumericsModel, java.lang.Cloneable, javax.swing.undo.StateEditable
    Direct Known Subclasses:
    AbstractAnimationModel
    public abstract class AbstractNumericsModel
extends AbstractModel
implements NumericsModel, Checkable
    An extension of AbstractModel which provides access to extended numerics functionality. Any plug-in models which will provide access to these features must extend AbstractNumericsModel.

      • getCategories

        public Category[] getCategories()
        Description copied from class: AbstractModel
        Retrieves the root Categories for this model type.

        The root categories are the top level parent categories that among them contain all the components in this model. This is not determines on an instance by instance basis. All instances of a particular model should have the same categories.

        Derivatives should take care to include AbstractModel's categories in their getCategories method.

        Overrides:
        getCategories in class AbstractModel

      • addComponent

        public void addComponent​(AbstractComponent component,
                         boolean adjustIdent)
        Description copied from class: AbstractModel
        Adds the given component to this model. The component's Category will be used to determine which internal list it is added to.

        If adjustIdent is true, a new ident will be assigned to the given component; if false, an ident will be assigned if the component's current ident is 0. If the component has a valid ident and adjustIdent is false, the top ident counter will be updated to include the component's current ident.

        Extending classes should ensure that AbstractModel.objectAdded(com.cafean.client.analysis.GenericObject, boolean) is called on each component that not passed to this method.

        Overrides:
        addComponent in class AbstractModel
        Parameters:
        component - the AbstractComponent to add.
        adjustIdent - if true, the given component will be treated as a new component to this model and given a new ident;

      • reconnectIdentReferences

        public void reconnectIdentReferences​(boolean preserveUnresolved,
                                     boolean useDbId)
        Description copied from class: AbstractModel
        Reconnects the ident references of this models directly contained objects. These objects include program options, model options, etc.

        Models that include root components are required to handle the reconnection of those components.

        Specified by:
        reconnectIdentReferences in interface IdentHolder
        Overrides:
        reconnectIdentReferences in class AbstractModel
        Parameters:
        preserveUnresolved - if true, ident references that aren't resolvable will be left dangling, if false, they will be set to 0.
        useDbId - if true, ident references will be reconnected via find_x_ByDB_ID; if false, ident references will be reconnected via find_x_ByIdent
        See Also:
        GenericObject.reconnectIdentReferences(boolean, boolean), AbstractModel.getNewComponentIdent(int, com.cafean.client.analysis.Category, boolean, boolean)

      • createCReal

        public CReal createCReal​(java.lang.String className,
                         ComponentElement ce)
        Create a CReal derivative whose class name matches the provided name. This allows reals to be reinstantiated solely by a stored class name, independent of any changes to package structure.
        Parameters:
        className - the simple class name of the the unit type to create. This can be retrieved from unit instances with the method getSimpleName() on the unit's Class object.
        ce - the AbstractComponent that should own the newly created unit.
        Returns:
        an instance of the unit type, or the result of getCRealDimensionless() if the class name cannot be matched.

      • findAccessor

        public Accessor findAccessor​(java.lang.String id)
        Returns the Accessor with the matching identifier, or null if not match is found. The default implementation searches for a SNAP Real Variable with a matching name (see SharedReal.getName()).

        Implementations should attempt to be at least "somewhat" efficient, as this method can be called frequently.

        Parameters:
        id - a String containing the ID of the desired Accessor
        Returns:
        the Accessor with the given ID

      • getAccessorDesc

        public java.lang.String getAccessorDesc​(java.lang.String id)
        Returns a short descriptive label for an Accessor that matches the given id, regardless of whether the matching component is in the model or not. If the given ID matches the syntax of an ID that can resolve in findAccessor, it must return a short description, even if the Accessor is not available (representing a deleted component, a disabled attribute, etc.). This mechanism is intended to provide descriptions of accessors in contexts such as error messages, particularly when a previously-valid ID no longer resolves.

        As an example, the default implementation decodes Shared Real numeric references such that the ID "Numeric:r1" returns the String "Shared Real r1".

        Implementations should call the super implementation when given an ID that cannot be parsed.

        Parameters:
        id - the ID of the Accessor (which may not currently exist)
        Returns:
        a brief label describing the indicated Accessor or INVALID_ACCESSOR_DESC if the ID cannot be parsed

      • getAccessorTypes

        public java.util.List<AccessorType> getAccessorTypes()
        Returns a List of AccessorType instances that describe Accessors available in this model. The default implementation returns an AccessorType that lists Shared Real numerics in the model. Implementations should make sure to add the contents of the super implementation to their results. This method shall not return null.
        Returns:
        a newly-allocated List of AccessorType instances
